      "writtenOn": "2019-08-19T21:30:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I had asked that the member be removed from this class so that it could serve as a pure interface. There are two style points that address this:\n\n1. Quite literally, interfaces must be pure and not bear their own data members or have their own implementations, except for a protected destructor as needed.\n\n2. Protected data members are prohibited.\n\nHere’s the discussion we had on this point: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/1745355/1/util/stream/output_stream.h#47. The part that we discussed was restricted solely to the use of the protected virtual destructor (which, to reiterate the above, is permitted to exist and have an implementation even in an interface class). That doesn’t constitute a waiver to permit a constructor implementation or any data members in this class.\n\noutput_stream_ should not be here (it belongs in the subclasses, and each subclass may manage as needed), nor should GetOutputStreamForTesting(). The only constructor should be a no-argument \u003ddefault. This header should not #include \u003cmemory\u003e.",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e8d44f41_dea4e09b",
        "filename": "util/stream/output_stream_interface.h",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 87,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000825
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-19T23:58:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I thought we have agreement on this implementation that is inline all implementation. (https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/crashpad/crashpad/+/1745355/1/util/stream/output_stream.cc)\n\nShall I go back to my previous suggestion, like below\n\nOutputStreamInterface (pure interface)\n\nOutputStreamBase : public OutputStreamInterface  {\n\n public:\n  OutputStreamInterface* GetOutputStreamForTesting() const {\n    return output_stream_.get();\n  }\n  \n protected:\n  OutputStreamInterface* output_stream() {\n      return output_stream_.get();\n  }\n\n private:\n  std::unique_ptr\u003cOutputStreamInterface\u003e output_stream_;\n}\n\nZlibOutputStream : public OutputStreamBase {\n}\n\nPlease help to confirm this.",
      "parentUuid": "ce70731a_d0282bc5",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c50aa38e_32ee9902",
        "filename": "util/stream/output_stream_interface.h",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 87,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-20T04:12:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I thought we have agreement on this implementation that is inline all implementation. (https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/crashpad/crashpad/+/1745355/1/util/stream/output_stream.cc)\n\u003e \n\u003e Shall I go back to my previous suggestion, like below\n\u003e \n\u003e OutputStreamInterface (pure interface)\n\u003e \n\u003e OutputStreamBase : public OutputStreamInterface  {\n\u003e \n\u003e  public:\n\u003e   OutputStreamInterface* GetOutputStreamForTesting() const {\n\u003e     return output_stream_.get();\n\u003e   }\n\u003e   \n\u003e  protected:\n\u003e   OutputStreamInterface* output_stream() {\n\u003e       return output_stream_.get();\n\u003e   }\n\u003e \n\u003e  private:\n\u003e   std::unique_ptr\u003cOutputStreamInterface\u003e output_stream_;\n\u003e }\n\u003e \n\u003e ZlibOutputStream : public OutputStreamBase {\n\u003e }\n\u003e \n\u003e Please help to confirm this.\n\nOutputStreamBase is not worth it. The only thing you’d be using it to share is a single constructor and member variable, and as I pointed out, access to that member variable from subclasses cannot be via direct access to a protected member, so you’d also need an accessor. The “shared” constructor doesn’t even help you out because each subclass would need to invoke the base constructor explicitly, where they could just as easily set a per-class member variable. It’s much more straightforward because the opportunity for sharing is so low to omit the unnecessary intermediate class and just have\n\nOutputStreamInterface  // abstract base\nZlibOutputStream : public OutputStreamInterface\nBase94OutputStream : public OutputStreamInterface\netc.",
      "parentUuid": "e8d44f41_dea4e09b",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
