    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3634a05f_393c608a",
        "filename": "util/stream/zlib_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 46,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-19T21:30:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Furthermore, with this structure, you actually can benefit from the non-DCHECK variant of InitializationState, because it’ll protect you against interface abuse if Write() fails due to inflateInit()/deflateInit() failing. You shouldn’t ever have to attempt to call those more than once.\n\nThis gives you much more control and better protection against interface abuse than a simple bool.\n\nHere’s how InitializationState is intended to be used in this situation:\n\nclass ZlibOutputStream {\n public:\n  bool ZlibOutputStream::Write(const uint8_t* data, size_t size) {\n    if (initialized_.is_uninitialized()) {\n      initialized_.set_invalid();\n\n      // do initialization stuff, return early if there’s a failure.\n      // if no failure:\n      initialized_.set_valid();\n    }\n\n    if (!initialized_.is_valid()) {\n      return false;\n    }\n  }\n\n private:\n  InitializationState initialized_;\n};",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "643d8744_3c1db734",
        "filename": "util/stream/zlib_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 46,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000825
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-19T23:58:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is very similar with patchset #3, just want to confirm you are fine to use InitializationState even without public Initialize() method, correct?",
      "parentUuid": "3634a05f_393c608a",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "33afdadf_fba4e110",
        "filename": "util/stream/zlib_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 46,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-20T04:12:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e This is very similar with patchset #3, just want to confirm you are fine to use InitializationState even without public Initialize() method, correct?\n\nYes, it’s OK.\n\nWe’re just whittling things down to the minimum required to do the job completely correctly, with an eye toward both readability and maintainability. Simplifying control flow like this eliminates bugs. (Example: the no-Write()-but-Flush() DCHECKing in earlier versions of this patch was probably caused by, and was certainly harder to spot because of, control flow more complex than necessary.)",
      "parentUuid": "643d8744_3c1db734",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
