      "writtenOn": "2019-08-19T21:30:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is better now.\n\nHowever:\n\n1. #define ZLIB_CONST or the equivalent in the build configuration would be even better than const_cast.\n\n2. If you broke the insistence on using void* for data and instead operated on uint8_t*, which is perfectly reasonable for byte-oriented data, you’d eliminate the need for the static_cast too.",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
