      "writtenOn": "2019-08-20T17:36:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Re 1: which build configuration you refer to? I found build/build_config.h which seems in chromium. Does it make sense to add it in util/misc/zlib.h?\n\nRe 2: change to Write\u0027 parameter to uint8_t.",
      "parentUuid": "3e033dc0_69196b21",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f626da78_cb24ac21",
        "filename": "util/stream/zlib_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 48,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-20T17:50:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Re 1: which build configuration you refer to? I found build/build_config.h which seems in chromium. Does it make sense to add it in util/misc/zlib.h?\n\nNo, there’s less of a guarantee of that having the desired effect (see below).\n\nI was thinking it’d be best to define it for the entire util library. You could put a “defines \u003d [\"ZLIB_CONST\"]” right here: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/1745355/5/util/BUILD.gn#182.\n\nOther locations can cause problems. You really only care about ZLIB_CONST being set for zlib_output_stream.cc, it’s irrelevant to other users of zlib_output_stream.h. But \u003czlib.h\u003e (its wrapper, actually) is #included by zlib_output_stream.h. Now you’re looking at an #include order problem, in the event that someone else includes \u003czlib.h\u003e (or its wrapper) without defining ZLIB_CONST before you have a chance to.",
      "parentUuid": "d642ee7e_d4d67df5",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "33d21127_c46793df",
        "filename": "util/stream/zlib_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 59,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-19T21:30:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What’s the desired handling if you reach Z_STREAM_END but continue to feed data into zlib? That input will be unconsumed.\n\nBy the same token, if you reach Z_STREAM_END with zlib_stream_.avail_in nonzero, there was unconsumed input to the decompressor.\n\nYou should handle these cases.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 59,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 59,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
