      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-19T21:30:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If you did want to memset(), you would do it much more easily from the constructor, by specifying in the initializer list: zlib_stream_().\n\nBut you don’t actually need to zero out the entire struct. inflateInit() and deflateInit() will set the entirety of the struct up appropriately, you only need to set a few values. See the zlib manual and our other zlib-using implementation in util/net/http_body_gzip.cc.",
      "revId": "fe231a5ef7e78ab56dcf18bb10a32d6b8f2e3a61",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
